text.tspan: Pulling the bar away from the resistor will cause an increase of flux in the wire loop
Lenzs Law states that the emf induced by this changing flux must produce a current
that opposes the change in flux. Therefore, via the right hand curl rule, the induced
current must flow counterclockwise to create a magnetic field going out of the page
